description:
In rx_thread() at lines 428-429:
```c
if (consecutive_errors < INT_MAX) {
    consecutive_errors++;
}
```

The check prevents overflow, which is good. However, INT_MAX is 2147483647. At LoRa data rates and 1000ms backoff, reaching INT_MAX would take ~68 years of continuous errors. This is effectively impossible.

SEVERITY: P4 - the overflow protection is unnecessary but harmless. The code is correct.

NO ACTION NEEDED - defensive coding, correct behavior.
